Lifecycle Events Streaming Pipeline

• Completed initial design and implementation framework for the Kafka-to-Iceberg streaming ingestion pipeline.

• Established project structure with modular components for configuration management, Kafka connectivity, event parsing, Iceberg table management, streaming listeners, health checks, and streaming writer.

• Implemented event parsing logic to extract key business attributes from lifecycle event messages:

* recon_id
* cob_date
* run_date
* processed_at timestamp (epoch conversion)

• Designed ingestion model to persist both business attributes and the complete source event payload for auditability and future schema evolution.

• Added Kafka metadata capture including topic, partition, offset, timestamp, and ingestion timestamp to support lineage and troubleshooting.

• Implemented empty-batch handling to prevent unnecessary Iceberg writes when no Kafka messages are available.

• Added streaming monitoring framework including query lifecycle listeners and Kafka connectivity validation.

• Defined production deployment approach for execution on Hadoop/YARN with Iceberg-backed storage on HDFS.

